name: Name
poetry_rating: How highly do you rate your own poetry?

name: Edgar Allan Poe
poetry:
Roses are red 
Violets are blue
I am the best poet
Much better than you
poetry_rating: 1 - Why did I even bother submitting.

name: William Shakespeare
poetry:
Why is it 33 degrees, 
In September,
I am hot.
poetry_rating: 7 - The most beautiful thing I've ever written.

name: Emily Dickinson
poetry:
Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall,
Humpty Dumpty had a great fall;
All the king's horses and all the king's men,
Couldn't put Humpty together again.

name: Elizabeth Barrett Browning
poetry:
Hi ho Hi ho,
Its home from work we go,
Whistles: do do do do dodododo,
Hi ho hi ho hi ho hi ho Hi ho,
Its home from work we go

name: Oscar Wilde
poetry:
The itsy bitsy spider crawled up the water spout.
Down came the rain, and washed the spider out.
Out came the sun, and dried up all the rain,
and the itsy bitsy spider went up the spout again.
